Colombia Stocks: Canacol, Enka, Mineros, Tablemac Gain

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-28T15:57:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/colombia-stocks-canacol-enka-mineros-tablemac-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:16 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.5 percent to 14,299.22, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.4 percent to 1,696.64.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  South America , rose 2.7 percent
to 2,325 pesos after saying it raised its 2011 production goal
to between 10,500 to 11,500 barrels of oil a day. The company
said in a regulatory filing today it raised its target this year
from a previous 10,000 to 11,000 barrels of oil a day.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB),  Colombia ’s biggest cement
maker and sixth-largest concrete maker in the U.S., rose 1.1
percent to 10,740 pesos after the company reported first-quarter
net income of 29 billion pesos ($16 million) in a regulatory
filing late yesterday. The company’s first-quarter cement sales
rose 27 percent from a year earlier to 1.2 million tons.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  , a Medellin-based synthetic
fibers producer, rose 0.7 percent to 13.8 pesos, after the
company said its first-quarter exports rose 33 percent from a
year ago to $17.6 million, according to a regulatory filing
yesterday.  Mineros SA (MINEROS)  , Colombia’s largest gold-mining
company, jumped 2.3 percent to 6,600 pesos, its highest in a
month, after saying it increased production by 49 percent to
28,760 ounces in the first quarter from a year ago, according to
a regulatory filing yesterday.  Tableros y Maderas de Caldas SA (TABLEMA)  , the wood
products maker known as Tablemac, jumped 2.7 percent to 11.6
pesos after the company said its first-quarter sales increased
32 percent from a year ago to a record 28 billion pesos,
according to a statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
